for there is no reason why the self- same things should not, at times, be expedient to two hostile parties ;
from which comes the saying that evils bring men together6, when the same thing hap- pens to be injurious to both.
That too is a good, which is not in excess7 ;
but whatever exceeds what it ought, is an evil.
