More, is so much, and somewhat besides.
2. Less, is that, which and somewhat else is so much.
3. Greater and more in number are laid only Comparatively to Less, and Fewer in number.
4.
Great and Little, Many and Few, are taken Compara­ tively to the Most of the same kind.
So that Great and Many, is that which exceeds;
Little and Few, is that which is ex ceeded by the Most of the same kind.
