ον may not mean undiluted wine, as for intemperate drinkers, but wine poured out rapidly.
But a thing is said metaphorically, as, The other gods and men 11 Slept all the night.
And at the same time he says :
For all is said metaphorically, instead of many, all12 being a species of many.
And thus οἴη δ’ἄμμορος is said of Orion metaphorically.
